determines who we'll become.

384
00:27:44,490 --> 00:27:45,640
You know well

385
00:27:46,110 --> 00:27:48,430
what you should do for now,

386
00:27:48,680 --> 00:27:50,100
and what you must get done.

387
00:27:51,310 --> 00:27:53,300
Is your dream still alive?

388
00:27:54,370 --> 00:27:57,250
I want you to do
what you intended to do

389
00:27:57,770 --> 00:28:00,120
and succeed like others.

390
00:28:01,500 --> 00:28:02,500
Therefore,

391
00:28:03,630 --> 00:28:04,730
focus on your practice

392
00:28:05,270 --> 00:28:06,430
and training.

393
00:28:07,960 --> 00:28:09,900
Everything else

394
00:28:10,360 --> 00:28:12,300
is pointless.

395
00:28:13,310 --> 00:28:14,310
Do you understand that?

396
00:28:20,070 --> 00:28:20,780
Yes, Mom.

397
00:29:26,570 --> 00:29:30,460
You've done a good job
frying eggs these days.

398
00:29:30,500 --> 00:29:32,640
- Thank you so much, Mom.
- They look great, honey.

399
00:29:36,390 --> 00:29:38,200
- Mmm...
- How is it?

400
00:29:38,290 --> 00:29:40,400
What a delicious fried egg this is.

401
00:29:40,440 --> 00:29:40,920
Yeah?

402
00:30:00,930 --> 00:30:03,770
One, two, three, four,

403
00:30:03,800 --> 00:30:07,120
five, six, seven, eight. Go.

404
00:30:10,500 --> 00:30:12,810
Aw... My baby...

405
00:30:12,920 --> 00:30:15,860
"He liked to visit his mom at the hospital."

406
00:30:16,240 --> 00:30:18,630
"But he would spend
so much time in the bathroom

407
00:30:18,930 --> 00:30:20,760
whenever he didn't want
to think about anything,

408
00:30:20,800 --> 00:30:25,260
letting the water run over his shoulders,
alone in the shower."

409
00:30:25,940 --> 00:30:28,710
"He saw him more often
than he saw his parents."

410
00:30:29,240 --> 00:30:32,150
"He drew both himself
and that man into it..."

411
00:30:32,230 --> 00:30:35,580
"He talked to him more than
he did to his own sibling."

412
00:30:35,840 --> 00:30:39,140
"They were in the same class
in high school."

413
00:31:07,300 --> 00:31:07,960
Let's go.

414
00:31:14,520 --> 00:31:15,750
- Here we come, Grandpa.
- Oh...

415
00:31:15,830 --> 00:31:18,220
Itthi and Ritt.
Very good of you to come.

416
00:31:18,260 --> 00:31:19,360
Here, here.

417
00:31:19,440 --> 00:31:21,150
This is Feng Shui Master Oumaim.

418
00:31:21,500 --> 00:31:23,130
She is a feng shui expert

419
00:31:23,160 --> 00:31:26,180
and our best landscape designer.

420
00:31:26,200 --> 00:31:28,340
Whoa, not really, sir.

421
00:31:28,460 --> 00:31:31,580
Actually, I just understand
how the land breathes

422
00:31:31,630 --> 00:31:34,430
and how energy flows.
That's all.

423
00:31:34,630 --> 00:31:37,320
I understand them well enough
to make design suggestions.

424
00:31:38,870 --> 00:31:39,620
That's great.

425
00:31:40,020 --> 00:31:42,030
Ritt's thesis is about this stuff.

426
00:31:42,820 --> 00:31:44,520
Please give him your advice.

427
00:31:44,850 --> 00:31:45,900
My pleasure.

428
00:31:46,640 --> 00:31:47,520
Thank you for your kindness.

429
00:31:48,990 --> 00:31:49,680
Let's start.

430
00:31:51,150 --> 00:31:51,960
Here,

431
00:31:52,300 --> 00:31:53,360
this project

432
00:31:53,770 --> 00:31:56,250
is located on the hill
facing strong winds.

433
00:31:56,280 --> 00:31:58,030
It's like riding a yawning dragon.

434
00:31:58,060 --> 00:32:02,140
The drawback of this project is that
we need rear structural support.

435
00:32:02,170 --> 00:32:05,890
♫Or is it destiny that decides?♫

436
00:32:05,910 --> 00:32:08,220
♫Is someone above drawing all these lines?♫

437
00:32:08,240 --> 00:32:13,760
♫Or playing matchmaker in disguise?♫

438
00:32:14,340 --> 00:32:18,590
♫What if the stars shift in their place♫

439
00:32:18,770 --> 00:32:22,270
♫Slightly out of line,♫

440
00:32:23,000 --> 00:32:26,690
♫Will our orbits still align?♫

441
00:32:53,050 --> 00:32:53,700
Mom!

442
00:32:57,960 --> 00:32:58,700
Mom!

443
00:33:02,410 --> 00:33:03,150
Mom.

444
00:33:06,330 --> 00:33:06,950
Mom!

445
00:33:07,590 --> 00:33:08,650
Mom!!

446
00:33:12,810 --> 00:33:14,160
Okay, let's start from the top.

447
00:33:14,360 --> 00:33:16,710
Five, six, seven, eight.

448
00:33:16,980 --> 00:33:20,850
♫I told you that maybe not yet♫

449
00:33:21,160 --> 00:33:23,370
♫Maybe not yet♫

450
00:33:23,590 --> 00:33:26,820
♫Maybe my feelings can't be contained♫

451
00:33:28,490 --> 00:33:30,720
♫My heart says♫

452
00:33:30,840 --> 00:33:32,640
♫I love you♫

453
00:33:33,090 --> 00:33:36,460
♫I don't know how to stop it♫

454
00:33:37,990 --> 00:33:40,620
Okay, let's take a break now
and practice later.

455
00:33:44,340 --> 00:33:45,550
Practicing on your own today?

456
00:33:45,840 --> 00:33:47,920
Why don't I see Pitcha?

457
00:33:48,170 --> 00:33:49,980
Pitcha isn't coming today, Pure.

458
00:33:50,340 --> 00:33:51,070
Yeah,

459
00:33:51,230 --> 00:33:52,320
he didn't answer my call,

460
00:33:52,540 --> 00:33:54,360
but he normally answers the phone.

461
00:33:57,170 --> 00:33:57,860
Ploy.

462
00:33:58,000 --> 00:33:59,400
Is Pitcha sick?

463
00:33:59,690 --> 00:34:01,840
Why didn't he come
to train you guys today?

464
00:34:01,960 --> 00:34:04,090
I called him already,

465
00:34:04,330 --> 00:34:05,900
but he didn't answer at all.

466
00:34:07,110 --> 00:34:09,159
Normally, he answers calls immediately.

467
00:34:09,409 --> 00:34:10,210
How strange.

468
00:34:11,120 --> 00:34:13,520
He's never disappeared like this before.

469
00:34:26,300 --> 00:34:28,210
Let's continue practicing
when you finish drinking.

470
00:34:48,340 --> 00:34:50,600
Oppa, saranghae.
Hello, kamsahamnida.

471
00:34:50,630 --> 00:34:51,710
How can I help you?

472
00:34:52,730 --> 00:34:55,730
Please tell everyone that I'm sorry
for not visiting the bar today.

473
00:34:56,730 --> 00:34:57,810
Are you okay?

474
00:34:58,210 --> 00:34:59,210
Are you sick or something?

475
00:34:59,500 --> 00:35:02,410
Have you seen the doctor yet?
Do you want me to buy you anything?

476
00:35:03,050 --> 00:35:04,310
My mom has been admitted to the hospital.

477
00:35:04,750 --> 00:35:06,670
Anyway, please tell Ployplern
that I'm sorry.

478
00:35:07,500 --> 00:35:09,490
I have to go now. Bye.

479
00:35:14,370 --> 00:35:16,100
Hey, Ploy. I'll be right back.

480
00:35:16,130 --> 00:35:17,370
What?! Where are you going?

481
